==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pulsate
<hw>Pul"sate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Pulsated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Pulsating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>pulsatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>pulsare</ets> to beat, strike, v.
intens. fr. <ets>pellere</ets> to beat, strike, drive. See
<er>Pulse</er> a beating, and cf. <er>Pulse</er>, <pos>v.</pos>]</ety>
<def>To throb, as a pulse; to beat, as the heart.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The heart of a viper or frog will continue to <qex>pulsate</qex>
long after it is taken from the body.</q> <rj><qau>E.
Darwin.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pulsatile</ent>⟦br⟧
